<taxonomicName id="4C7424938D20FFC7FD85F993FD09A844" box="[636,766,1547,1573]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Phragmites" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90083028D20FFC7FD85F993FD09A844" box="[636,766,1547,1573]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">Phragmites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), cereals, clover (
<taxonomicName id="4C7424938D20FFC7FC2AF993FBB4A844" box="[979,1091,1547,1573]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="1" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90083028D20FFC7FC2AF993FBB4A844" box="[979,1091,1547,1573]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">Trifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C7424938D20FFC7FBA4F993FEDFA824" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Paspalum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dilatanum">
<emphasis id="B90083028D20FFC7FBA4F993FEDFA824" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">Paspalum dilatanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, oat (
<taxonomicName id="4C7424938D20FFC7FE88F9B4FE4CA827" box="[369,443,1580,1606]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Avena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90083028D20FFC7FE88F9B4FE4CA827" box="[369,443,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">Avena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), soya beans, wheat (
<taxonomicName id="4C7424938D20FFC7FD46F9B4FCD1A824" box="[703,806,1580,1605]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Triticum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90083028D20FFC7FD46F9B4FCD1A824" box="[703,806,1580,1605]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">Triticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), as well as apple, blackberry, rose, tea in different locations of 
<collectingCountry id="F3631F808D20FFC7FE16F9D3FDBAA807" box="[495,589,1611,1638]" name="Georgia" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">Georgia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49B091F28D20FFC7FDA2F9D3FD55A807" box="[603,674,1611,1638]" country="Georgia" name="Ajaria" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">Ajara</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F3631F808D20FFC7FD4CF9D3FCD1A807" box="[693,806,1611,1638]" name="Germany" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">Germany</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3631F808D20FFC7FCC8F9D3FC4BA807" box="[817,956,1611,1638]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3631F808D20FFC7FC3EF9D3FBE4A807" box="[967,1043,1611,1638]" name="Russia" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49B091F28D20FFC7FBDBF9D3FF11A8E7" country="Russia" name="Krasnodar" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">Krasnodar Region</collectingRegion>
), and 
<collectingCountry id="F3631F808D20FFC7FED4F9F3FE55A8E7" box="[301,418,1643,1670]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
during 1957–1973 by several collectors.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB5F108D20FFC7FF1AF913FB27A8A7" blockId="1.[174,1232,1481,1734]" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">
D e s c r i p t i o n. Female. Dorsal shield (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D20FFC7FD59F913FD2DA8C7" box="[672,730,1675,1702]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[266,1143,474,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-14@2.[223,1167,435,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Neoseiulus bicaudus (Wainstein). Female:A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F — spermatheca; G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I, genu II (setal abbreviation: ad — antero-dorsal, pd — post-dorsal; al — antero-lateral, pl — post-lateral; av — antero-ventral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454837/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, A) elongated, with constrictions at level of R1, weakly sclerotized, with thin net-like sculpture areas better evident on posterior part of
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB5F108D20FFC7FF1AF96DFD7AA96D" blockId="1.[227,1043,1781,1858]" box="[227,653,1781,1804]" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">
<superScript id="7C01F2588D20FFC7FF1AF96DFF1DA963" attach="left" box="[227,234,1781,1794]" fontSize="5" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">1</superScript>
See more details in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE522E18D20FFC7FE31F96EFD7EA96D" author="Demite, P. R. &amp; Moraes, G. J. de &amp; McMurtry, J. A. &amp; Denmark, H. A. &amp; Castilho, R. de" box="[456,649,1782,1804]" pageId="1" pageNumber="296" refId="ref6819" refString="Demite, P. R., Moraes, G. J. de, McMurtry, J. A., Denmark, H. A. &amp; Castilho, R. de C. 2016. Phytoseiidae Database. http: // www. lea. esalq. usp. br / phytoseiidae /. Last update: September 2016." type="url" year="2016">Demite et al. (2016)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB5F108D20FFC7FF1AF888FD5CA946" blockId="1.[227,1043,1781,1858]" box="[227,683,1808,1831]" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">
<superScript id="7C01F2588D20FFC7FF1AF888FF1DA97C" attach="left" box="[227,234,1808,1821]" fontSize="5" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">2</superScript>
Correct spelling of this geographical name.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB5F108D20FFC7FF1AF8B2FBE4A923" blockId="1.[227,1043,1781,1858]" box="[227,1043,1834,1858]" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">
<superScript id="7C01F2588D20FFC7FF1AF8B2FF1DA956" attach="left" box="[227,234,1834,1847]" fontSize="5" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">3</superScript>
Hereinafter data lacking on the original slide labels are added in square brackets.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB5F108D23FFC4FF5FFF37FE8DAFEB" blockId="2.[166,1225,175,394]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">
shield, 7 pairs of small solenostomes (
<emphasis id="B90083028D23FFC4FDA6FF37FC27AEA8" box="[607,976,175,201]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">gd1, gd2, gd4, gd5, gd6, gd8, gd9</emphasis>
), 16 pairs of poroids, and 17 pairs of setae acute, thin, short and slightly different in length except Z5 elongated. Dorsal setae smooth except S4, S5, Z4, Z5 weakly serrated. Setae Z5 much longer than others postlateral setae S4, S5, Z4. Seta j3 equal to distance of seta z2 but not extend beyond it. Setae z2 and z4 half of distance to bases of next setae. Seta Z4 longer than distance to solenostome 
<emphasis id="B90083028D23FFC4FEB9FED7FE9EAF08" box="[320,361,335,361]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">gd9</emphasis>
and equal to distance to base of following seta S5. Setae J5 acute, short and smooth (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D23FFC4FEF6FEF7FEBDAFEB" box="[271,330,367,394]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[266,1143,474,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-14@2.[223,1167,435,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Neoseiulus bicaudus (Wainstein). Female:A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F — spermatheca; G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I, genu II (setal abbreviation: ad — antero-dorsal, pd — post-dorsal; al — antero-lateral, pl — post-lateral; av — antero-ventral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454837/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, B).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF0B0F988D23FFC4FF5FF943FDD5A920" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454837" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6454837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454837/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" startId="2.[166,199,1755,1777]" targetBox="[266,1143,474,1718]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8BCB5F108D23FFC4FF5FF943FDD5A920" blockId="2.[166,1225,1755,1857]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">
Fig. 1. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7424938D23FFC4FF1CF943FDD7A890" authority="(Wainstein)" baseAuthorityName="Wainstein" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[229,544,1755,1777]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" genus="Neoseiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicaudus">
<emphasis id="B90083028D23FFC4FF1CF943FE53A891" box="[229,420,1755,1776]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">Neoseiulus bicaudus</emphasis>
(Wainstein)
</taxonomicName>
. Female: A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D 
<emphasis id="B90083028D23FFC4FEE9F96FFED1A96D" box="[272,294,1783,1804]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">—</emphasis>
chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F — spermatheca; G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I, genu II (setal abbreviation: 
<emphasis id="B90083028D23FFC4FD73F889FD55A947" box="[650,674,1809,1830]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">ad</emphasis>
— antero-dorsal, 
<emphasis id="B90083028D23FFC4FCACF889FC9AA947" box="[853,877,1809,1830]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">pd</emphasis>
— post-dorsal; 
<emphasis id="B90083028D23FFC4FBF2F889FBEAA947" box="[1035,1053,1809,1830]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">al</emphasis>
— antero-lateral, 
<emphasis id="B90083028D23FFC4FF5FF8B3FF4FA921" box="[166,184,1835,1856]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">pl</emphasis>
— post-lateral; 
<emphasis id="B90083028D23FFC4FEA8F8B4FE90A920" box="[337,359,1836,1857]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">av</emphasis>
— antero-ventral).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF0B0F988D22FFC5FF57FD18FC2DACF7" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454841" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6454841" box="[174,986,640,662]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454841/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" startId="3.[174,207,640,662]" targetBox="[348,1091,183,596]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8BCB5F108D22FFC5FF57FD18FC2DACF7" blockId="3.[174,986,640,662]" box="[174,986,640,662]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">
Fig. 2. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7424938D22FFC5FF17FD18FDDDACF7" authority="(Wainstein)" baseAuthorityName="Wainstein" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[238,554,640,662]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" genus="Neoseiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicaudus">
<emphasis id="B90083028D22FFC5FF17FD18FE59ACF4" box="[238,430,640,661]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">Neoseiulus bicaudus</emphasis>
(Wainstein)
</taxonomicName>
. Male: A — chelicera; B — ventrianal shield.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BCB5F108D22FFC5FF1AFD65FC3BADF9" blockId="3.[174,1233,765,1848]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">
All ventral setae thin, acute, and smooth with the exception of seta JV5 weakly serrated. Sternal shield with 3 pairs of setae (St1–St3) and 2 pairs of lyrifissures. Setae St4 on separate metasternal platelets each with pore (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D22FFC5FD25FCA5FCECAD39" box="[732,795,829,856]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[266,1143,474,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-14@2.[223,1167,435,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Neoseiulus bicaudus (Wainstein). Female:A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F — spermatheca; G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I, genu II (setal abbreviation: ad — antero-dorsal, pd — post-dorsal; al — antero-lateral, pl — post-lateral; av — antero-ventral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454837/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, C). Genital shield with pair of seta (Ge). Narrow transversal sclerotized stria between genital and ventrianal shields. One pair narrow straight-line plates posteroparaxially to setae ZV1 (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D22FFC5FCA6FCE5FC6DADF9" box="[863,922,893,920]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[266,1143,474,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-14@2.[223,1167,435,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Neoseiulus bicaudus (Wainstein). Female:A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F — spermatheca; G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I, genu II (setal abbreviation: ad — antero-dorsal, pd — post-dorsal; al — antero-lateral, pl — post-lateral; av — antero-ventral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454837/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, C).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB5F108D22FFC5FF1AFC05FE31ABF9" blockId="3.[174,1233,765,1848]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">
Ventrianal shield wider than genital shield, elongated, with convex anterior margin, near sub-triangular with lateral constrictions, all finely striated. Three pairs of short preanal setae JV1, JV2, ZV2, one pair of para-anal (Pa) and unpaired post-anal setae (Pst) on ventrianal shield (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D22FFC5FE7DFC65FE35AA79" box="[388,450,1021,1048]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[266,1143,474,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-14@2.[223,1167,435,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Neoseiulus bicaudus (Wainstein). Female:A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F — spermatheca; G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I, genu II (setal abbreviation: ad — antero-dorsal, pd — post-dorsal; al — antero-lateral, pl — post-lateral; av — antero-ventral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454837/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, C). Pre-anal solenostomes (
<emphasis id="B90083028D22FFC5FCE4FC65FCB3AA76" box="[797,836,1021,1047]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">gv3</emphasis>
) small, round and disposed posteroparaxially of setae JV2 (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D22FFC5FE17FB85FDDEAA59" box="[494,553,1053,1080]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[266,1143,474,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-14@2.[223,1167,435,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Neoseiulus bicaudus (Wainstein). Female:A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F — spermatheca; G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I, genu II (setal abbreviation: ad — antero-dorsal, pd — post-dorsal; al — antero-lateral, pl — post-lateral; av — antero-ventral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454837/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, C). Four pairs of setae, ZV1, ZV3, JV4 and JV5, 4 pairs of small oval platelets on the integument surrounding the ventrianal shield. Chelicerae normal in size. Fixed digit with 6 (7 on digit of other chelicera) denticles equal in size in two separate rows (
<quantity id="4C8CF2F58D22FFC5FED1FBE5FEA1AAF9" box="[296,342,1149,1176]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
distal and 4 or 
<quantity id="4C8CF2F58D22FFC5FDFEFBE5FDC4AAF9" box="[519,563,1149,1176]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
medial row), movable digit with 1 tooth (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D22FFC5FBECFBE5FBA7AAF9" box="[1045,1104,1149,1176]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[266,1143,474,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-14@2.[223,1167,435,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Neoseiulus bicaudus (Wainstein). Female:A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F — spermatheca; G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I, genu II (setal abbreviation: ad — antero-dorsal, pd — post-dorsal; al — antero-lateral, pl — post-lateral; av — antero-ventral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454837/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, D). Metapodal plates elongate, anterior platelet smaller and narrower than posterior plate (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D22FFC5FB9EFB05FB55AAD9" box="[1127,1186,1181,1208]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[266,1143,474,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-14@2.[223,1167,435,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Neoseiulus bicaudus (Wainstein). Female:A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F — spermatheca; G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I, genu II (setal abbreviation: ad — antero-dorsal, pd — post-dorsal; al — antero-lateral, pl — post-lateral; av — antero-ventral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454837/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, E). Infundibulum of spermatheca cup-shaped, atrium large, cervix short (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D22FFC5FC1BFB25FBEAAAB9" box="[994,1053,1213,1240]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[266,1143,474,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-14@2.[223,1167,435,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Neoseiulus bicaudus (Wainstein). Female:A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F — spermatheca; G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I, genu II (setal abbreviation: ad — antero-dorsal, pd — post-dorsal; al — antero-lateral, pl — post-lateral; av — antero-ventral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454837/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, F). Peritremes long, extending forward to level of bases of setae j1 (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D22FFC5FCECFB45FCA6AA99" box="[789,849,1245,1272]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[266,1143,474,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-14@2.[223,1167,435,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Neoseiulus bicaudus (Wainstein). Female:A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F — spermatheca; G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I, genu II (setal abbreviation: ad — antero-dorsal, pd — post-dorsal; al — antero-lateral, pl — post-lateral; av — antero-ventral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454837/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, A). Posterior part of peritremal shield curved and pointed (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D22FFC5FE0BFB65FDD9AB79" box="[498,558,1277,1304]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[266,1143,474,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-14@2.[223,1167,435,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Neoseiulus bicaudus (Wainstein). Female:A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F — spermatheca; G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I, genu II (setal abbreviation: ad — antero-dorsal, pd — post-dorsal; al — antero-lateral, pl — post-lateral; av — antero-ventral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454837/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, G). Leg IV with three smooth acute macrosetae: longest on basitarsus, short on tibia and genu (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D22FFC5FD89FA85FD5CAB59" box="[624,683,1309,1336]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[266,1143,474,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-14@2.[223,1167,435,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Neoseiulus bicaudus (Wainstein). Female:A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F — spermatheca; G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I, genu II (setal abbreviation: ad — antero-dorsal, pd — post-dorsal; al — antero-lateral, pl — post-lateral; av — antero-ventral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454837/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, H). Macrosetae on other legs missing. Genu II with 7 setae (2 
<emphasis id="B90083028D22FFC5FEA4FAA6FE9CAB36" box="[349,363,1342,1367]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">a</emphasis>
–2 
<emphasis id="B90083028D22FFC5FE69FAA5FE5AAB36" box="[400,429,1341,1367]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">ad</emphasis>
, 2 
<emphasis id="B90083028D22FFC5FE36FAA5FE1BAB36" box="[463,492,1341,1367]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">pd</emphasis>
/ 0 
<emphasis id="B90083028D22FFC5FDE1FAA6FDC4AB36" box="[536,563,1342,1367]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">av</emphasis>
, 0 
<emphasis id="B90083028D22FFC5FDAFFAA6FD86AB36" box="[598,625,1342,1367]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">pv</emphasis>
–1 
<emphasis id="B90083028D22FFC5FD6CFAA5FD5CAB36" box="[661,683,1341,1367]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">pl</emphasis>
) (setae: 
<emphasis id="B90083028D22FFC5FCF4FAA5FCDDAB36" box="[781,810,1341,1367]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">ad</emphasis>
— antero-dorsal, 
<emphasis id="B90083028D22FFC5FC06FAA5FBEBAB36" box="[1023,1052,1341,1367]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">pd</emphasis>
— post-dorsal; 
<emphasis id="B90083028D22FFC5FF57FAC5FF33AB16" box="[174,196,1373,1399]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">al</emphasis>
— antero-lateral, 
<emphasis id="B90083028D22FFC5FE6CFAC5FE5CAB16" box="[405,427,1373,1399]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">pl</emphasis>
— post-lateral; 
<emphasis id="B90083028D22FFC5FD9BFAC6FD8AAB16" box="[610,637,1374,1399]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">av</emphasis>
— antero-ventral); seta 
<emphasis id="B90083028D22FFC5FC6DFAC5FC4FAB16" box="[916,952,1373,1399]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">al2</emphasis>
shorter than other setae on the segment (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D22FFC5FE89FAE5FE41ABF9" box="[368,438,1405,1432]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[266,1143,474,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-14@2.[223,1167,435,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Neoseiulus bicaudus (Wainstein). Female:A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F — spermatheca; G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I, genu II (setal abbreviation: ad — antero-dorsal, pd — post-dorsal; al — antero-lateral, pl — post-lateral; av — antero-ventral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454837/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">fig. 1I</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB5F108D22FFC5FF1AFA05FD9AA839" blockId="3.[174,1233,765,1848]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">
Measurements. Length of dorsal shield from j1 to end of shield, Lds 400; width of dorsal shield at R1 level, Wds 180; length of ventrianal shield, Lvas 135; max width of ventrianal shield, Wvas 117; distance between pre-anal solenostomes gv3, Lgv3 38; length of tarsus of leg IV, Ltar IV 104. Length of setae: j1 25, j3 31, j4 15, j5 15, j6 17, J2 21, J5 14, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE4039D78D22FFC5FB76FA65FB3CA879" box="[1167,1227,1533,1560]" degrees="4" direction="south" minutes="34" orientation="latitude" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" precision="925" value="-4.5666666">s4 34</geoCoordinate>
, z2 23, z4 20, z5 14, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE4039D78D22FFC5FE73F985FE3CA859" box="[394,459,1565,1592]" degrees="2" direction="south" minutes="35" orientation="latitude" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" precision="925" value="-2.5833333">S2 35</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE4039D78D22FFC5FE2FF985FDE1A859" box="[470,534,1565,1592]" degrees="4" direction="south" minutes="43" orientation="latitude" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" precision="925" value="-4.7166667">S4 43</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE4039D78D22FFC5FDD8F985FD96A859" box="[545,609,1565,1592]" degrees="5" direction="south" minutes="45" orientation="latitude" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" precision="925" value="-5.75">S5 45</geoCoordinate>
, Z1 20, Z4 40, Z5 98, r3 34, R1 30, JV5 63; macrosetae on leg IV, MCh IV: ge 27, ti 32, tar 73.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB5F108D22FFC5FF1AF9C5FDAAA899" blockId="3.[174,1233,765,1848]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">
Male from 
<typeStatus id="54CFE1B28D22FFC5FE92F9C5FE6AA819" box="[363,413,1629,1656]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">type</typeStatus>
locality unknown. Non-type male, mentioned above has been studied and drawn here. Dorsal setal pattern in general as in female, chelicera as in 
<figureCitation id="134F43958D22FFC5FB92F9E5FB5FA8F9" box="[1131,1192,1661,1688]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,640,662]" captionTargetBox="[348,1091,183,596]" captionTargetId="figure-541@3.[329,1099,174,606]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Neoseiulus bicaudus (Wainstein). Male: A — chelicera; B — ventrianal shield." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454841" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454841/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">fig. 2</figureCitation>
, A; fixed digit of chelicerae with 5 denticles, movable digit with 1 denticle; spermatodactyle L-shaped; ventrianal shield reticulated with 3 pairs of setae and one pair of small round pre-anal solenostomes 
<emphasis id="B90083028D22FFC5FE45F945FE13A896" box="[444,484,1757,1783]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">gv3</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="134F43958D22FFC5FE0BF945FDD8A899" box="[498,559,1757,1784]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,640,662]" captionTargetBox="[348,1091,183,596]" captionTargetId="figure-541@3.[329,1099,174,606]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Neoseiulus bicaudus (Wainstein). Male: A — chelicera; B — ventrianal shield." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454841" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454841/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">fig. 2</figureCitation>
, B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB5F108D22FFC5FF1AF965FDC0A959" blockId="3.[174,1233,765,1848]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">
As opposite to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE522E18D22FFC5FE6DF965FD96A979" author="Wainstein, B. A." box="[404,609,1789,1816]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" pagination="236 - 240" refId="ref7639" refString="Wainstein, B. A. 1962. New predatory mites of the family Phytoseiidae (Parasitiformes) of the fauna of the USSR. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 41 (1), 236 - 240 [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="1962">Wainstein (1962)</bibRefCitation>
who indicated only one macrosetae, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7424938D22FFC5FBEEF966FB55A976" baseAuthorityName="Wainstein" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[1047,1186,1789,1815]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" genus="Neoseiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicaudus">
<emphasis id="B90083028D22FFC5FBEEF966FB55A976" box="[1047,1186,1789,1815]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">N. bicaudus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has really three macrosetae on leg IV.
</paragraph>
